	<text>
		<body>
			<div>
				<pb facs="#facs_1" n="1"/>
				<p facs="#facs_1_tr_1">
					<lg>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_1"><orgName ref="gnd-1044992484">Department of Philosophy</orgName></l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_2"><placeName ref="geo-12750417">MCGILL UNIVERSITY</placeName></l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_3"><placeName ref="geo-6077243">MONTREAL</placeName> 2</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_4"><date to="1948-05-23" from="1948-05-23" when="1948-05-23">May 23rd, 1948</date>.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_5">My dear <persName ref="gnd-116183853">Getrud Bing</persName>,</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_6">I hope you have had a few restful</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_7">days. At last, the examinations are over,</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_8">and I can write a few lines.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_9">TRANSLATION OF <persName ref="gnd-118519522">ERNST CASSIRER</persName>: I in</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_10">formed <persName ref="gnd-1157950825">Mr. F. David Hoeniger</persName> - the man in</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_11"><placeName ref="geo-6167865">Toronto</placeName> who is "planning to translate 'Die</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_12">Platonische Renaissance in England' into</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_13">English" - that the translation rights are</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_14">vested in the <orgName ref="gnd-37543-3">Warburg Institute</orgName>. I asked him</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_15">if he had found a publisher; if so, the pub-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_16">lisher should get in touch with the Institute</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_17">to discuss the terms. I also told him that X</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_18">I had heard that the book was already translate</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_19">ted and that I was trying to obtain confirmat-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_20">ion of this.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_21">I have the impression that Mr. Hoeni-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_22">ger's project is fairly vague. Should he be</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_23">serious and have found a publisher, it can't</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_24">do harm if that publisher makes you an offer.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_25">I have also written to <placeName ref="geo-4959019"><orgName ref="gnd-1094478-3">Bowdoin</orgName></placeName> Colle-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_26">ge, asking <persName ref="gnd-171253949">Professor Koelln</persName> for details about</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_27">Mr. Pettibridge's translation. It seems that</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_28">P. has been unable, during all these years,</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_29">to find a translator.  - Now that some of Cas-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_30">sirer's works have appeared in U.S.A., it may</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_31">well be that a publisger could be found. He</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_32">would naturally have to apply to you.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_33">I shall see <persName ref="gnd-118667386">Mrs. Toni Cassirer</persName> in the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_34">near future. If you could let me know (quite</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_35">informally and subject to later precision)</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_36">what your views are about the granting of</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_37">translation rights in this case, it would give</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_40">me some guidance. I imagine you would like</l>
					</lg>
				</p>
				<pb facs="#facs_2" n="2"/>
				<p facs="#facs_2_tr_2">
					<lg>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_1">to have some royalty (or outright purchase sum?)</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_2">for the Institute, though not a high one?</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_3">I could bring up the matter when I am in<placeName ref="geo-4846179"> <placeName ref="geo-5015627">Yale</placeName>.</placeName></l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_4">(The <orgName ref="gnd-5262965-X">Yale</orgName> or the <orgName ref="gnd-5096712-5">Princeton Press</orgName> would be the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_5">most likely ones).</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_6"><choice><orig>MELENCOLIA</orig><reg>dd</reg></choice>. When I am in <placeName ref="geo-5128581">New York</placeName>, I would</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_7">willingly go to <placeName ref="geo-5102922">Princeton</placeName>, to discuss the mat-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_8">ter with <persName ref="gnd-118591568">Panofsky</persName>. I don't like the man much</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_9">and don't foresce that I shall revise my opinion</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_10">to any appreciable extent. But I think I shall</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_11">get along with him, and it is worth a little</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_12">effort on my part if it helps the publication.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_13">Could you perhaps let me know some time how far</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_14">the matter has progressed, and what remains to be</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_15">done ? - I will try to get him to do his part;</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_16">if I fail, no harm will have been done. It</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_17">would mean carte blanche for us; and, I believe,</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_18">all could be done in a fairly friendly way.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_19"><choice><orig>PLATO ARABUS</orig><reg>Überlieferung von Platons Werken im arabischen Raum </reg></choice>. No time yet to write you at</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_20">length. I received a telegram from <persName ref="gnd-1029912939">Lotte</persName> saying</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_21">that in the Plato Arabus report <choice><orig>W.</orig><reg>Unbekannte Person, vmtl Betreuer von Mr. Lewis, Islamforscher?</reg></choice> put in the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_22">announcement that Mr. Lewis - a student who</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_23">works under W's supervision - is going to edit</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_24">the <choice><orig>Theologia Aristotelis</orig><reg>Arabische Übersetzung und Bearbeitung von Teilen der Enneaden des Neuplatonikers Plotin</reg></choice>. Here again, I had</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_25">not been informed, and the whole matter was un-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_26">der discussion last year, when <persName ref="gnd-116719583">Father Henry</persName> (the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_27">Jesuit, Professor at the Inst. Catholique in Pa-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_28">ris) vame to see <persName ref="gnd-118804898">Saxl</persName> and me, to ascertain in</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_29">which form he could co-operate?  It would obvious</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_30">ly be an insult to Henry and, as we promised him</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_31">to pursue the matter, a breach of faith if he</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_32">were left out altogether. I cabled <persName ref="gnd-1029912939">Lotte</persName> last</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_33">night to add: "Negotiations are in progress</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_34">Professor Henry, of <placeName ref="geo-2792482">Louvain</placeName>,</l>
						<choice><orig><l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_36">who is preparing the critical edition of Ploti-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_37">nus, concerning the mode of his co-operation in</l></orig><reg>Projekt von Henry, Grundlage für Theologie Aristotelis-Vergleich</reg></choice>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_38">establishing the relation between the Greek Plo-</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_39">tinus text and the Theologia Aristotelis." From</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_40">the point of view of scholarship - both for the</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_41">Greek Plotinus and for our Arabic Theologia -</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_42">his co-operation is essential. The announcement</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_43">in this form will not prejudice anything; to</l>
						<l facs="#facs_2_tr_2_tl_44">leave it out, would be indefensible.,</l>
					</lg>
				</p>
			</div>
